organizations.name: smiley n. pool/the dallas morning news

text:
Comment on This Story Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) hurdles Philadelphia Eagles free safety Rodney McLeod (23) during the first half of an NFL football game at AT&T Stadium on Sunday, Oct. 30, 2016, in Arlington. (Smiley N. Pool/The Dallas Morning News) By SportsDayDFW.com Contact SportsDayDFW.com on Twitter: @SportsDayDFW 
The Dallas Morning News sends award-winning photographers to every Dallas Cowboys game to capture the team's best moments. Here are their best shots of rookie running back Ezekiel Elliott so far this season: The beginning Staff Photographer Running back Ezekiel Elliott, who played for Ohio State, stands for a photograph after participating in an interview after he was introduced by the Dallas Cowboys after being drafted fourth overall in the 2016 NFL draft by the Cowboys at the team's headquarters in Irving, Texas, Friday April 29, 2016. (Andy Jacobsohn/The Dallas Morning News) Zeke remembers the Titans Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys fan and actor Denzel Washington (left) visits with Dallas Cowboys rookie running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) following afternoon practice at training camp in Oxnard, California, Saturday, August 6, 2016. Washington spent the practice in the field tower with Jones. (Tom Fox/The Dallas Morning News) Did we just become best friends?! Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott (4) congratulates Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) on a 60 yard rushing touchdown during the second half of play at AT&T Stadium in Arlington on Sunday, October 9, 2016. The Dallas Cowboys defeated the Cincinnati Bengals 28-14. (Vernon Bryant/The Dallas Morning News) The crop top Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) celebrates with fans after the Cowboys won 35-10 on Sunday, November 6, 2016 at FirstEnergy Stadium in Cleveland, Ohio. (Ashley Landis/The Dallas Morning News) A sight we're all getting used to Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) signals first down after a run play during the second half of play at FedEx Field in Landover, Maryland on Sunday, September 18, 2016. The Dallas Cowboys defeated the Washington Redskins 27-23. (Vernon Bryant/The Dallas Morning News) Run, Zeke, Run! Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) breaks away for a 60 yard touch down in the third quarter during the NFL football between the Cincinnati Bengals and Dallas Cowboys at AT&T Stadium on Oct. 9, 2016 in Arlington, Texas. Cowboys win 28-14. (Ting Shen/The Dallas Morning News) You want Zeke in your hair? Say no more, fam Smiley N. Pool/Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys fan Juan Ramirez of San Antonio sports a haircut featuring running back Ezekiel Elliott before an NFL football game against the Detroit Lions at AT&T Stadium on Monday, Dec. 26, 2016, in Arlington, Texas. (Smiley N. Pool/The Dallas Morning News) Zeke feeds Zeke Ashley Landis/Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) and wide receiver Dez Bryant (88) laugh at a cutout of Elliott before their game against the Detroit Lions on Monday, December 26, 2016 at AT&T Stadium in Arlington, Texas. (Ashley Landis/The Dallas Morning News) Zeke giving back Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott presents a puppy named Tico to Mia Ruiz after her family adopted the dog at the SPCA of Texas on Monday, Oct. 17, 2016, in Dallas. Elliott sponsored a $21 "Run to the Shelter" pet adoption day on Monday. For each pet adoption, Elliott is covering the difference of the cost after the adopting family pays its $21. The event is part of the SPCA of Texas' 'Dogtober' promotion. 21 refers to Elliott's jersey number. (Smiley N. Pool/The Dallas Morning News) Zeke gives back, part two Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) serves an early Thanksgiving Day meal to guest Christopher Campbell (right) at the Salvation Army's Mabee Social Service Center in Fort Worth, Texas Monday November 14, 2016. The Dallas Cowboys cheerleaders and mascot Rowdy joined the players. (Andy Jacobsohn/The Dallas Morning News) Quiet moments before a game Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) prays in the end zone before the opening kickoff at the Baltimore Ravens vs. the Dallas Cowboys NFL football game at AT&T Stadium in Arlington, Texas on Sunday, November 20, 2016. (Louis DeLuca/The Dallas Morning News) Dez knew Tom Pennington/Getty Images ARLINGTON, TX - DECEMBER 26: Ezekiel Elliott #21 of the Dallas Cowboys runs for a touchdown as teammate Dez Bryant #88 celebrates as the Cowboys play the Detroit Lions during the first half at AT&T Stadium on December 26, 2016 in Arlington, Texas. (Photo by Tom Pennington/Getty Images) #FeedZeke Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott celebrates after picking up a first down during the first half of an NFL football game against the Philadelphia Eagles at AT&T Stadium on Sunday, Oct. 30, 2016, in Arlington. (Smiley N. Pool/The Dallas Morning News) Leading the NFL in rushing is hard work Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) rests on the turf as he warms up before their game against the Baltimore Ravens on Sunday, November 20, 2016 at AT&T Stadium in Arlington, Texas. (Ashley Landis/The Dallas Morning News) The kettle Tom Pennington/Getty Images ARLINGTON, TX - DECEMBER 18: Ezekiel Elliott #21 of the Dallas Cowboys celebrates after scoring a touchdown by jumping into a Salvation Army red kettle during the second quarter against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers at AT&T Stadium on December 18, 2016 in Arlington, Texas. (Photo by Tom Pennington/Getty Images) Zeke busts a move Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) dances for the camera after scoring a fourth-quarter touchdown during the Washington Redskins vs. the Dallas Cowboys NFL football game at AT&T Stadium in Arlington, Texas on Thursday, November 24, 2016. (Louis DeLuca/The Dallas Morning News) Hurdles! Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott (21) hurdles multiple defenders. (Staff photos/The Dallas Morning News) Turtle shell? Tom Pennington/Getty Images ARLINGTON, TX - DECEMBER 26: Ezekiel Elliott #21 of the Dallas Cowboys struggles to take off his jersey and shoulder pads after the Dallas Cowboys beat the Detroit Lions 42-21 at AT&T Stadium on December 26, 2016 in Arlington, Texas. (Photo by Tom Pennington/Getty Images) Tackling...a fan? Stephen M. Dowell/TNS NFC running back Ezekiel Elliott tackles a fan who ran onto the field during the NFL Pro Bowl on Sunday, Jan. 29, 2017 at Camping World Stadium in Orlando, Fla. The AFC won the game, 20-13. (Stephen M. Dowell/Orlando Sentinel/TNS) Dancing with Dez Tom Pennington/Getty Images ARLINGTON, TX - JANUARY 15: Dez Bryant #88 and Ezekiel Elliott #21 of the Dallas Cowboys warm up on the field prior to the NFC Divisional Playoff game against the Green Bay Packers at AT&T Stadium on January 15, 2017 in Arlington, Texas. (Photo by Tom Pennington/Getty Images) Let me tell you bout my best friend Roger Steinman/AP Dallas Cowboys' Ezekiel Elliott, left, and Dak Prescott, center, joke around as they give an on air interview after an NFL football game against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Sunday, Dec. 18, 2016, in Arlington, Texas. (AP Photo/Roger Steinman) Throw up the X Smiley N. Pool/Staff Photographer Dallas Cowboys running back Ezekiel Elliott celebrates after scoring on a 55-yard touchdown run against the Detroit Lions during the first half of an NFL football game at AT&T Stadium on Monday, Dec. 26, 2016, in Arlington, Texas. (Smiley N. Pool/The Dallas Morning News) In these photos Elliott is wearing an orange bracelet, that says SILVER STRONG in honor of Jake Silver, a boy who has bone cancer.
